      },
    ],
    comment: '<p>The <code>npm adduser</code> command is used to create and verify users in the specified registry. The credentials will be saved to the <code>.npmrc</code> file.</p>\n<p>Username, password and email values aren\'t specified as command arguments, but are asked and read in from prompts.</p>\n<p>Additional configuration  arguments specified with flags are <code>registry</code>, <code>scope</code> and <code>always-auth</code>.</p>\n<p>The first, <code>registry</code> indicates the <strong>base URL</strong> of the npm package registry:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-bash">npm adduser --registry=http://myreg.com\n</code></pre>\n<p>If <code>scope</code> is specified, the registry will only be used for packages with that scope:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-bash">npm adduser --registry=http://myreg.com\n    --scope=@myScope\n</code></pre>\n<p>The <code>always-auth</code> is by default set to <code>false</code>, but if specified, all requests to the given registry should include authorization information as an authorization header:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-bash">npm adduser --registry=http:myreg.com\n    --always-auth\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note that <code>npm login</code> is an alias for <code>npm adduser</code> and works in exactly the same way.</p>\n',
  },
